From e8c9f47450748f61628a5760ed6c66e808032634 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Karl-Erik Gustafsson <ke.gustafsson@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 09:21:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Delete prompt2 (#63)

* feat(appstore): add plugin removal confirmation with data preservation option

Replace browser confirm() dialog with a styled Bootstrap Modal that shows
plugin data size and lets users choose whether to keep or delete plugin
configuration and data files. Default is to preserve data (safe default).

Adds GET /appstore/datasize/:name endpoint to calculate plugin data size,
and extends the remove endpoint to accept a deleteData parameter.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01KuBQxKn17sPSDvnxTLZqBF

* fix(appstore): async filesystem ops, symlink safety, and cleanup

- Convert getDirectorySize and getPluginDataSize to async using
  fs.promises to avoid blocking the event loop on HTTP requests
- Use lstat instead of stat to prevent following symlinks in
  directory size calculation
- Remove cleanupAfterRemove from module.exports (internal detail)
- Add GB tier to formatBytes utility

https://claude.ai/code/session_01DK47Pa6tLMsZzzoXj85Dzp

---------

Co-authored-by: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
